<section id="about">
<h2>About Me</h2>
<p>I am Raima Sing, a recent graduate with an
Integrated MSc (2019-24) in Life Sciences from the National
Institute of Science Education and Research (NISER),
Bhubaneswar, India. My Master's thesis focused on
investigating the role of cold-sensitive TRP ion channels in
microglial function and iron homeostasis.
I am currently working as a project student
investigating how TRP channels regulate microglial iron
homeostasis and its possible role in neurodegeneration. I
aspire to conduct transformative research that improves the
lives of individuals affected by chronic disorders while
advancing societal health and well-being.</p>
</section>
<section id="scholarship">
<h2>Funding</h2>
<p>I was the recipient of the prestigious DISHA
Scholarship (2019-24) from the Department of Atomic Energy
(DAE), the government of INDIA</p>
</section>
<section id="research">
<h2>Research Experience</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Master's Thesis:</strong>
Explored the role of TRPM8 ion channels in microglial function
and iron homeostasis.</li>
<li><strong>Project Student:</strong>
NISER, Bhubaneswar, India (06/2024 – Present)
<ul>
<li><strong>Supervisor:</strong>
Prof. (Dr). Chandan Goswami</li>
<li><strong>Project 1:</strong>
Investigating the role of TRP in neurodegeneration.
<ul>
<li><strong>Key
findings:</strong> Modulation of TRP channels regulates
microglial iron homeostasis.</li>
<li><strong>Techniques
used:</strong> Cell culture, Live-cell Confocal microscopy,
Immunocytochemistry, Optimized MTT assays, and Image
analysis.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Project 2:</strong>
Characterizing endogenous TRPM8 activator.
<ul>
<li><strong>Key
findings:</strong> Ca²⁺ imaging using GCaMP shows the
endogenous activator is functional in neuronal and microglial
cells and impacts organelle functions.</li>
<li><strong>Techniques
used:</strong> Cell culture, Confocal microscopy, Instant
Ca2+ imaging, Transformation and transfection, and Image
analysis.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Summer Internship:</strong>
Advance Centre for Treatment Research and Education in Cancer
(ACTREC), Mumbai, India (5/2020 – 07/2020)
<ul>
<li><strong>Supervisor:</strong>
Prof. (Dr). Jayant Sastri Goda</li>
<li>Could not continue due to
COVID-19 pandemic.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>R.K. University, Rajkot, India
(07/2020 – 09/2020)</strong>
<ul>
<li><strong>Supervisor:</strong>
Dr. Vijay Kumar</li>
<li><strong>Project:</strong>
Conducted in-depth research on probiotics and prebiotics,
enhancing understanding of gut microbiota.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Winter Internship:</strong>
NISER, Bhubaneswar, India (12/2022–01/2023 &
12/2023–01/2024)
<ul>
<li><strong>Supervisor:</strong>
Prof. (Dr). Chandan Goswami</li>
<li><strong>Project 1:</strong>
Explored the role of thermosensitive ion channels during
cholesterol depletion in activated and resting microglial
cells.
<ul>
<li><strong>Key
findings:</strong> TRPM8 localization in lipid raft is
dependent on membrane cholesterol level.</li>
<li><strong>Techniques
used:</strong> Cell culture, Confocal microscopy, Hydrogels,
Image analysis and statistics, IF staining, cholesterol
reduction assay, Bacterial transformation, and
transfection.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Project 2:</strong>
Studied modulation of thermosensitive TRP ion channels using
hydrogels in neuronal cells.
<ul>
<li><strong>Key
findings:</strong> Modulation of TRP ion channels affects
organelle function in the presence of hydrogel.</li>
<li><strong>Techniques
used:</strong> 2D cell culture using hydrogels, Confocal
microscopy, Image analysis and statistics.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</section>
